<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<%- include('../partials/top.ejs', {pagename: "Login"}) %>
		
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="/login/login.css" media="screen" />

		<script
			src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"
			integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4="
			crossorigin="anonymous"
		></script>
		<script src="/login/login.js"></script>
	</head>

	<body>
		<%- include('../partials/nav.ejs')%>

		<main>
			<div class="multicolumn">
				<h1>Ready to find a tutor?</h1>

				<div class="form">
					<h2>Log in</h2>
					<form method="POST" action="/api/login" class="login" id="login-form">
						<div id="login-error" class="login-error"></div>
						<input
						  name="user"
						  type="email"
						  id="login-email"
						  class="login-field"
						  placeholder="email..."
						/>
						<input
							name="pass"
							type="password"
							id="login-password"
							class="login-field"
							placeholder="password..."
						/>
						<!-- <hexagonal-button class="strong">
								<label for="login-submit">
				
								</label>
							<button-top>Login</button-top>
						</hexagonal-button> -->
						<input
							type="submit"
							id="login-submit"
							value="Login"
							class="login-button"
						/>
						<div class="login-bottom">
							<div>
								Don't have an account?
								<a href="/register">Register</a>
							</div>
							<div>
								Lost your password?
								<a href="/resetpassword">Reset your password</a>
							</div>
						</div>
					</form>
				</div>

				<article class="not-main">
					<h2>FAQ</h2>
					<dl>
						<dt>Is the program free?</dt>
						<dd>Yes, the program is entirely free. We are a non-profit organization and we do not charge fees for our services. If you are pleased with our services, please consider supporting us with a donation!</dd>
						<dt>What subjects can I find help with?</dt>
						<dd>Our tutors can help you with English, science, social studies, and math; we invite you to look at our full list of subjects after logging in. If possible, please send your tutor any material such as textbooks, homework, or notes prior to the tutoring session so they can preview the material and teach you more effectively.</dd>
						<dt>Can I work with the same tutor again?</dt>
						<dd>Absolutely! You can schedule multiple sessions with your tutor, even if it is your first time signing up.</dd>
					</dl>
					<p>
						<a href="/#faq">Other FAQ</a>
					</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</main>

		<%- include('../partials/footer.ejs')%>
	</body>
</html>